<br>
We can get into semantics over what &quot;lifestyle&quot; and &quot;addiction&quot; mean. I won't... I start fires, not control them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  However, I would argue that EQ does have redeeming qualities in that it does force a certain amount of socialization to occur, it can build up people skills, organizational skills. It is a different mode of existance. So what. Theres no logic in denigrating it.<br>
